-- Ivory Coast Cocoa-Bean Exports Rise 53% in December
-- B y   B a u d e l a i r e   M i e u
-- 2012-02-08T09:27:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/ivory-coast-cocoa-bean-exports-rise-53-in-december-table-.html
Cocoa-bean exports from the port of
Abidjan in  Ivory Coast , the world’s largest producer of the
chocolate ingredient, increased 53 percent in December,
according to data from the harbor.  Shipments rose to 125,816 metric tons in December from
82,082 tons in the same period a year earlier, according to the
figures. Exports of cocoa products increased to 20,237 tons from
15,21 tons, the port’s data showed.  Ivory Coast’s main harvest runs from October through March
while a mid crop is collected from April through September. The
following is a breakdown of exports of processed cocoa products
from the port of Abidjan, the commercial capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
